<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="153" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="153">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="153">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1917" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Meotipa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Meotipa pulcherrima" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulcherrima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">Meotipa pulcherrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. capacifaba" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="capacifaba">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. capacifaba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Li, Liu, Xu &amp; Yin, 2020 (see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3956/2020-96.3.177" author="Li, CM" journalOrPublisher="Pan-Pacific Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" pagination="177 - 184" refId="B8" refString="Li, CM, Liu, JX, Xu, X, Yin, HQ, 2020. A new species of spider in the genus Meotipa Simon, 1895 (Araneae: Theridiidae) from southern China. Pan-Pacific Entomologist 96 (3): 177 - 184, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3956/2020-96.3.177" title="A new species of spider in the genus Meotipa Simon, 1895 (Araneae: Theridiidae) from southern China." url="https://doi.org/10.3956/2020-96.3.177" volume="96" year="2020">Li et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
: figs 1A-J, 2A-E, 3A-E) by shared characters such as raised eyes, raised carapace posteriorly, and spherical copulatory ducts (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Meotipa pulcherrima (Mello-Leitao, 1917) A-C female habitus (flattened black spines on the abdomen and legs were broken off during photography) (A dorsal B prolateral C ventral). D-H epigynum (D ventral, on the body, and the arrow points to tongue-shaped apophysis E, F in alcohol E ventral F dorsal G, H in gum arabic G ventral H dorsal). Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C); 0.1 mm (D-H). Abbreviations: CD = copulatory duct, FD = fertilization duct, S = spermathecae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.75400.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/636293" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">2G</figureCitation>
), but it can be distinguished from the latter by the following characters: (1) the copulatory openings are inconspicuous in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. pulcherrima" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="pulcherrima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. pulcherrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Meotipa pulcherrima (Mello-Leitao, 1917) A-C female habitus (flattened black spines on the abdomen and legs were broken off during photography) (A dorsal B prolateral C ventral). D-H epigynum (D ventral, on the body, and the arrow points to tongue-shaped apophysis E, F in alcohol E ventral F dorsal G, H in gum arabic G ventral H dorsal). Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C); 0.1 mm (D-H). Abbreviations: CD = copulatory duct, FD = fertilization duct, S = spermathecae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.75400.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/636293" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">2D</figureCitation>
), but obvious in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. capacifaba" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="capacifaba">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. capacifaba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3956/2020-96.3.177" author="Li, CM" journalOrPublisher="Pan-Pacific Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" pagination="177 - 184" refId="B8" refString="Li, CM, Liu, JX, Xu, X, Yin, HQ, 2020. A new species of spider in the genus Meotipa Simon, 1895 (Araneae: Theridiidae) from southern China. Pan-Pacific Entomologist 96 (3): 177 - 184, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3956/2020-96.3.177" title="A new species of spider in the genus Meotipa Simon, 1895 (Araneae: Theridiidae) from southern China." url="https://doi.org/10.3956/2020-96.3.177" volume="96" year="2020">Li et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 2A); (2) the posterior margin of atrium has a tongue-shaped protrusion medially in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. pulcherrima" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="pulcherrima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. pulcherrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Meotipa pulcherrima (Mello-Leitao, 1917) A-C female habitus (flattened black spines on the abdomen and legs were broken off during photography) (A dorsal B prolateral C ventral). D-H epigynum (D ventral, on the body, and the arrow points to tongue-shaped apophysis E, F in alcohol E ventral F dorsal G, H in gum arabic G ventral H dorsal). Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C); 0.1 mm (D-H). Abbreviations: CD = copulatory duct, FD = fertilization duct, S = spermathecae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.75400.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/636293" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">2E</figureCitation>
), but not in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. capacifaba" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="capacifaba">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. capacifaba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3956/2020-96.3.177" author="Li, CM" journalOrPublisher="Pan-Pacific Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" pagination="177 - 184" refId="B8" refString="Li, CM, Liu, JX, Xu, X, Yin, HQ, 2020. A new species of spider in the genus Meotipa Simon, 1895 (Araneae: Theridiidae) from southern China. Pan-Pacific Entomologist 96 (3): 177 - 184, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3956/2020-96.3.177" title="A new species of spider in the genus Meotipa Simon, 1895 (Araneae: Theridiidae) from southern China." url="https://doi.org/10.3956/2020-96.3.177" volume="96" year="2020">Li et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 2A); (3) the conductor is broad with a sharp point in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. pulcherrima" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="pulcherrima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. pulcherrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1155/1962/32404" author="Levi, HW" journalOrPublisher="Psyche, Cambridge" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" pagination="209 - 237" refId="B7" refString="Levi, HW, 1962. More American spiders of the genus Chrysso (Araneae, Theridiidae). Psyche, Cambridge 69 (4): 209 - 237, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1155/1962/32404" title="More American spiders of the genus Chrysso (Araneae, Theridiidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1155/1962/32404" volume="69" year="1962">Levi 1962</bibRefCitation>
: figs 74, 75), but relatively narrow with a blunt point in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. capacifaba" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="capacifaba">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. capacifaba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3956/2020-96.3.177" author="Li, CM" journalOrPublisher="Pan-Pacific Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" pagination="177 - 184" refId="B8" refString="Li, CM, Liu, JX, Xu, X, Yin, HQ, 2020. A new species of spider in the genus Meotipa Simon, 1895 (Araneae: Theridiidae) from southern China. Pan-Pacific Entomologist 96 (3): 177 - 184, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3956/2020-96.3.177" title="A new species of spider in the genus Meotipa Simon, 1895 (Araneae: Theridiidae) from southern China." url="https://doi.org/10.3956/2020-96.3.177" volume="96" year="2020">Li et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
: figs 2D, 3D).
</paragraph>
